MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Flying through the blizzard in a mysterious flying snowmobile.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Hyahaaaaa! Shibuya-san is the strongest and the fastest today too☆

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Hyahaha~! Desunano~♪

While being slightly taken back by the two of them who seem to be having so much fun, I cling desperately to the body of the snowmobile so that I don't get shaken off. Usually I'm in the role of carrying everyone on the train, so this position is a bit new to me.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Be careful not to fall off, Goshujin! When it's snowing like this, it's hard to find and catch you on the way down!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: That's right, be careful or you'll be in trouble~? If you fall from here, you'll be flat no~?
Why is this snowmobile flying in the first place...? Doesn't it go against the laws of physics?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Ehehe~, isn't it Santa-like?♪
That's true, but. I'm afraid I don't understand the logic.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Hmmm. To put it simply, this snowmobile is fly with my buoyancy~

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Udon-chan, your whole body radiates buoyancy magic. That's why you float around and can't even dive underwater.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Yes~. I'm in the swim club, but I can't even dive.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: And there's more. Recently, I've been practice with the swim team and train with the SSS, and it seems that my buoyancy is getting stronger.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: If I really get my buoyancy up~, hey hey♪ Throw a lot of heavy containers on the snowmobile is just a piece of cake!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: We're making use of Udon-chan's special ability(?) to create a completely new kind of flying delivery business! In our company!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: There's so much snow on the ground that even ordinary horse-drawn carriages can't move, and it's difficult to transport supplies, which are in short supply all over the world, unless we do this.
I see. Flying delivery companies... Once this kind of thing becomes commonplace, even the Mist Train will be obsolete.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Doubtful it'll become common, will it? This is a method that relies completely on Udon-chan's special abilities, you know?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Udon-chan, from what I've heard, is an ancient person who time-traveled ahead in time from long ago, right? It's rare to find such a person anywhere else, isn't it?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Yes~. Unfortunately, I have never met anyone in my position~

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I don't remember much about the time I was there originally... I'd like someone who knows what they're talk about to tell I about the past.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I don't even know where I was born and raised, a pity.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: That must be difficult too~ Not only are there no other ancient people, but there seems to be very little ancient knowledge left behind.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Even when I asked 3000 years old Chitose obaa-san, she told me that the things from that time period are 'long ago' for her too.
Super-ancient times, far before 3,000 years? For us, it was a time of unidentified ruins, railway lines and the like.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: What are the railway tracks for, anyway? Thanks to them, trains can run, which is a great help to us as the SSS, right?
I don't know how to respond to your 'what'. That's one of the biggest mysteries in the world that even I can't answer.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Ummm... I wish I could have remembered things like when the railway line was built and all that.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: It's no use asking for something you don't have! You have to do the best you can with what you can get your hands on.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: AHA! Don'cha think you're barking up the wrong tree!?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: WAGYAH!?

Suddenly, a new member of the Special Steel Squad, 'Shitamachi no Dai Oyabun', Oshiage appeared from the depths of the blizzard, surprising us. The snowmobile came to a sudden halt, and Shibuya asked frothily on her purpose.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: O-O-Oshiage anebo! Wh-Wha-Why are you floating in the air!?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I thought we were going to crash...! I didn't expect you to fly in the sky, anego's rockin' as always!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I'm the one who should be saying 'ya rock'. Why are ya flying around so high up in the sky like a bird or a winged insect?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I thought ya'll are flying monsters that's gonna attack me, I was so chilled.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Uhuhu, not a monster ya~? It's Santa~, here here♪
Oshiage softened her expressions, then got curious watching as Udon Thani was showing off her cute outfit.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: What're ya, this kiddo? Friend of yers, Shibuya-chan?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Osu! This is my part-time friend Udon-chan!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Heeh, that's quite a tasty name♪ Good good, wanna eat some kaminari-okoshi?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I'll have some~! I get hungry when I'm float! Munch munch♪

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Anego~, please don't feed my part-timer friend, okay?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Anego？ Shibuya anego's anego, meaning super anego?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Ah, I'm a steeplejack from downtown, Oshiage at'cha service. While in the SSS, I'm ya junior methinks.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: You're my junior? Wow, I'm finally the senior I've always want to be...☆

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Aha! Whaat~ an innocent and cute girl 'ere♪

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Isn't that right? She's very popular as our company's mascot character these days! We're planning to make her into merchandise too! The first one is a 'Talking Udon-chan Alarm Clock'!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Udooon~, Udooon~! I'll let you know when it's six in the morning~!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Ahaha, like the saying of the samurai that pretends he has eaten well when he has no food, Shibuya-chan's family's rich and noble yet doing a business like that huh.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Well... Normally I'm just a reeegular delivery person, but now is the time of year for that, so I'm dressed as Santa.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: This kind of thing is called cosplay, isn't it?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: That's whacha learned from Akibo, innit? ...Thanks for being good friends with that girl, Shibuya-chan♪

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: It's my pleasure too! Shibuya-chan very happy to be friends with Akiba-chan! She's also been very helpful in teaching me about cosplay and how to have fun at work!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Oya. You look like you're having fun, but you're not too keen on your job.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I'm enjoying it now~, but at first I wasn't very motivated.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Honestly, I didn't want to work at all, Shibuya-san had run away from home half of the time and was doing whatever I wanted, so I should at least help out in the family business to show my filial piety~ That's what my otou-san told me.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Hmm, ya have a lot of things going on beneath your easy-going face, aren' cha? But it's a blessing that your parents are still alive, so you should be filial to them at your best.

Come to think of it, Oshiage, you didn't know who your parents were because you suddenly 'appeared' one day in a state where you had lost your memories before your teenage years. In that respect, your position's a bit similar to Udon Thani's.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I see~? So you are also an ancient...?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I don't think it's that funny. I'm just a common street gangster wandering round downtown.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: --EACHOOO! Argh, stutard! God dammit!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I'm gonna catch a cold if I talk in such cold weather. If ya don't mind, ya can come to my foothold after ye've finished your work.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: It's because I've something wonderful that makes your body warm. So, I'd love to have a relaxing chat over tea.

Looking closely, it seems that Osiage, like a steeplejack, had dexterously balanced herself on a very high ladder and climbed up to such a high altitude. The fact that she didn't even sway in spite of the blizzard is a true feat of craftsmanship.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Udon Thani
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Super anego's feet? What are you stand on? Umm~ umm~, it's hard to see because there's so much blizzard~?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Shibuya
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: There's still plenty of time left, so if you're curious, why don't you go and have a look?

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oshiage
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Well, I won't force you. A child's a wind child, an energetic child, flyin' around as one pleases♪
After saying this, Oshiage easily climbed down the ladder. She is the very essence of the free wind.
